DESCRIPTION:Admission is free\, open to the public. Learn more about this 
 exhibition\n \nThis multi-generational panel celebrates the distinguished
  women alumni of Montclair. Featuring exhibiting artists Nancy Bergman Pa
 ntirer ’80\, Tiffany Perez ’09\, and Maria Valdivia ’24 in conversation a
 bout their careers and creative practices\, moderated by curator Sally Mo
 rgan Lehman.\n \nCarpe Diem: Select Alumni in the Visual Arts is a group 
 exhibition presented by the Office for Development and Alumni Engagement 
 and hosted by the University Galleries. Carpe Diem brings together twelve
  accomplished alumni working in a range of media.\n \nCurated by Sally Mo
 rgan Lehman\, who has taught in the Department of Art and Design at Montc
 lair and is owner and director of Morgan Lehman Gallery in New York City\
 , Carpe Diem highlights the breadth of artistic practices fostered at Mon
 tclair and the lasting impact of its visual arts alumni.\n \nFeatured art
 ists include Flávia Berindoague ’13\, Bisa Butler ’05\, Jonathan Calm ’97
 \, Kyle Coniglio ’10\, Alyssa Fanning ’12\, Allen Ginsberg (1943)\, Márta
  Kucsora (2005–06)\, Michael Manning ’11\, Nancy Bergman Pantirer ’80\, T
 iffany Perez ’09\, William Pope.L ’78\, and Maria Valdivia ’24.\n\nHosted
  by: Montclair State University Galleries\n\nAdditional Information can b
 e found at: https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12095893
