DESCRIPTION:Lead Change in Child Advocacy and Policy When children and fam
 ilies face complex challenges\, they need informed\, compassionate profes
 sionals to stand up\, speak out\, and shape solutions. If you're ready to
  turn your commitment into action\, we're here to help. We're hosting a v
 irtual panel featuring alumni from our program on March 19 at 6:00 PM (ES
 T). This is a no-pressure\, exploratory space to hear directly from profe
 ssionals who were once in your shoes and determine if our program fits yo
 ur goals. This session will cover the following programs: \n\nOnline Mast
 er of Arts in Child Advocacy and Policy\nChild Advocacy (Certificate) – O
 nline\n\nWhy Montclair? Completing the certificate program allows you to 
 transfer all 15 credits towards the Master of Arts in Child Advocacy\, in
  accordance with all related graduate policy.\n\nHosted by: The Office of
  Graduate Admissions\n\nOnline Location: https://graduate.montclair.edu/r
 egister/?id=8e33994e-2628-459e-825c-7657bde894a9\n\nAdditional Informatio
 n can be found at: https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/11964300
